      We will choose an $\eta$ such that we get a crossing point at $\sim 0.4807$ and then we will find an appropriate $\nu$ for the scaling collapse.

      Determination of 𝜈ν and 𝜂η

      • 𝜒/𝐿2−𝜂χ/L2−η
      • 𝑚max/𝐿2−𝜂2mmax/L2−η2

      All the above quantities include R and P-type regions on same footing.

      We will choose an 𝜂η such that we get a crossing point at ∼0.4807∼0.4807 and then we will find an appropriate 𝜈ν for the scaling collapse.
